28/09/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Following a cabinet meeting Tuesday (27 September), Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis announced that the government would seek a special parliamentary debate on foreign policy issues, chiefly the launch of EU membership negotiations with Turkey on 3 October. 
Molyviatis reiterated the government stance that the talks with Turkey should begin as scheduled. 
He also noted that the negotiation framework for Turkey stipulates the positions of both Greece and Cyprus. 
(ANA, MPA - 27/09/05)
